<div id="review_2168830958" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2168830958" />
    <a title="Mike Gowan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17806011-mike-gowan"><img alt="Mike Gowan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1391967379p2/17806011.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2168830958?book_show_action=true">Oct 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mike Gowan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mike Gowan" href="/user/show/17806011-mike-gowan">Mike Gowan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2168830958" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3953618187444471522">I liked it. I was a little thrown off by the author&apos;s trick of showing a critical scene but not dropping the name of the character. He&apos;s a bit like Agatha Christie in that respect, except Doss&apos; scenery is southern Colorado and his people are cowboys and Southern Ute Indians on the reservation. At any rate, I accepted the challenge and tried to figure out who dunnit and who it got done to. In that spirit, the plotting is very clever and makes a lot of sense. I&apos;ll read more of this authors&apos; myster</span>
  <span id="freeText3953618187444471522" style="display:none">I liked it. I was a little thrown off by the author's trick of showing a critical scene but not dropping the name of the character. He's a bit like Agatha Christie in that respect, except Doss' scenery is southern Colorado and his people are cowboys and Southern Ute Indians on the reservation. At any rate, I accepted the challenge and tried to figure out who dunnit and who it got done to. In that spirit, the plotting is very clever and makes a lot of sense. I'll read more of this authors' mysteries.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3953618187444471522" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2168830958">
  <td colspan="2">
